<title>USA: Tecnomatix debt over-allotment exercised.</title>
<headline>Tecnomatix debt over-allotment exercised.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-08-18</dateline>
<text>
<p>Tecnomatix Technologies Ltd, a computer engineering software maker, said Monday the managing underwriters of its offering of 5-1/4 percent convertible subordinated notes due 2004 had excercised an over-allotment option on $12.75 million of the notes.</p>
<p>The company, based in Herzliya, Israel, said the aggregate principal amount of the debt offering now totals $97.75 million.</p>
<p>Tecnomatix said its proceeds would be used for working capital and general corporate puchases, which may indclude acquisitions.</p>
